 work out a plan of action and - go into a shop - to see if we could skim something off it you know. And what we stole in our own way - I've seen me coming back - my mother she said, get two apples, I've seen me coming back with four. A pound of tatties, 
c
oming back with a peck, that's a - half a stone I think. Things like that, see we used to nab it, steal 'em in the shop you know. Pretty cheap, but then people must have thought they was nae stealing, you know, you'd get a turnip for about a penny or thre
ehapence, now you're - well, two bob. Carrot, cabbage, a ha'penny, a ha'p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5984429\charrsid3767953 enorth of cabbage and turnip. Ha\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
