ry. I think he paid a shilling a month or something, and he got as many books as he liked for that month, you know, as long as he fetched the other ones back, back and forth. I used to have to go. My father worked and says Tim I canna go up the library to
n
ight, get they books and - go up the library and pick some more, I used to pick books for him. Well I had to go so - well, I was able to read as well and understand things a bit better than - my brothers and sisters, and I seemed most capable you know. Bu
t I -
